main event: Multiple unidentified objects were observed over Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada on March 20, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were observed for 15-20 minutes.
No photographs were taken of the objects.
The objects were observed moving west-northwest.
The report mentions multiple observers, including Mr. and Mrs. C. Gillis of Doctors Cove, Nova Scotia.
The objects were described as a 'bright light in the sky' that left a trail of sparks and possible gray smoke as it passed overhead.
witnesses: Multiple observers, including Mr. and Mrs. C. Gillis
